		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <span id=>Anonymous</span></a><b><span id=></span></b>
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</nobr><br><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Anonymous&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>I myself have made a Human Bertox SK on Norrath for no better reason than to help a friend Kill Koalindl fish... well, I got hooked and am stuck with the name Koakila Fishgutter at lvl 33.&nbsp;&nbsp;=)<br>At any rate, faction is just as good for Bertox as I'm supposing it is for Inno.  I have had no problems finding guilds to train in any city I've ventured to thus far.  This includes FP, Neriak, Ogguk and (of course) Qeynos.  Needless to say, you shouldn't have a problem finding a guild to train in across the Continent (however to get in and out of the large races cities you need invis which you get at lvl 30).  This eliminates the talk of faction and such.  Since this was all you were concerned about... I would simply chose a city you'd rather start in.  It is true that Qeynos sewers are an Excellent place to hunt as it is never crowded (often you find you're the only one on) and provides many useful noobie equipment like +5 hp rings and earings... a good cloak and a reasonable ac 2 +3 cha necklace.  Now that the warrens has opened up... it gives you an even greater chance for easy xp and good armor.  Go to the warrens around lvl 6 or so... collect them Kobold molars and go collect your ringmail.  Easy and simple xp and cash (I've a noob friend start an Erud SK and he's up to abour 100 plat at lvl 8 from all the loot in there).  If, however, you do choose to stay in the Qeynos area, you can get easy faction and xp killing gnolls and doing gnoll teeth/moonstone quests.  xp's about the same as molars (maybe a little less) and reward's not as good, but at least gnoll teeth stack.<br><br>My 2cp,<br>Koakila 33 SK, Luclin</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td class=mhback align=right><span class=mh id=fs8><a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=5><img src=/shared/root_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Up" width=17 height=11> Thread Index</a> |  <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=5&post=1><img src=/shared/new_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="New" width=17 height=11> New Subject</a> | <a class=mh href=/db/classes.html?class=5&mid=98512549275781&num=5&page=&post=1&mid=98512549275781><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply" width=17 height=11> Reply to Thread</a></span></td></tr><tr><td><table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" class="mform"><tr><td id="fs8">5 Posts [ <a href="/fsearch.html?base=class5">Search Forums</a> ]</nobr></td></tr></table>&nbsp;</td></tr>
